locality: Dpto. Rio Negro: Neblina Camp 10: 12.5 km NNW of Pico Phelps (=Pico Neblina), 16.25 km NE of Base Camp; Heliamphora-Neblinaria savana with Euterpe swamps along streams. In Euterpe swamp. Whole plant to 3 m tall, arching.
Territorio Federal Amazonas: Norte de Pico Phelps. Marshy almost treeless plateau with elevated margins. Approximate coordinates; 0ยบ56'N, 65ยบ58'W, elev. 2200 m.

Dpto. Rio Negro; Camp II, 2.5-3.5 km NE of Pico Phelps (=Neblina). Boggy valley with Heliamphora, Sphagnum and gallery forest of Euterpe, Podocarpus, slopes with shrubby vegetation of Bonnetia, Weinmannia; erect, 2.8 m tall, common but mostly less than 1 m tall and sterile. Inflorescence purplish.
Trilha da Bacia do Gelo para o Pico. Campo de altitude arbustivo com brejos de Saxofrederia. Parque Nacional do Pico da Neblina
